<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99323219539450></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99323219539450><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=2&mid=99323219539450>RE: Footwear for the Wee ones</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2&mid=99323219539450#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=3172><span id= >Ybolla</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>30 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jun 22nd 1:49 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, I have taken up tailoring (wish I had thought of it 8 levels ago when I was gettin exp for killing spiderlings. I really coulda used saving the cash on bandages, oh well :P). Just FYI: Ruined makes Tattered, MQ and HQ make Studded and Reinforced (I think LQ makes only containers-like small tailored bag ect..) but you need the help of a Blacksmith to make the Studs and Boning for those types of Tailored armor. As far as I have been able to find out LEATHER (just straight-up, plain ole Leather) cannot be player crafted. <br>Tattered looks green, which goes better with my outfit than the metal looking Ring.<br>Thats it<br>&nbsp;<br>The only constant in the universe is change.</td></tr>
