	   <tr><td colspan=2>sorry, young rogue, you don't get to choose your loot.&nbsp;&nbsp;when you're snatching coins from someone's pocket, it's impossible to tell which are which...sometimes it's a shiny gold one, sometimes a tarnished copper, and sometimes you can even pinch a platinum.  you're not just limited to coins...other items your target is carrying are also fair game...but chance decides what you'll get.  <br><br>if this character is going to be your main, then think about the type of rogue you really want to be--do you want to be a "battle" rogue or a "stealth" rogue.  dwarves and barbarians make good battle rogues, while halflings and dark elves make good stealth rogues.  more important, though, is to pick a race you will want to play...if you don't want to look like a dumpy dwarf(no offense meant to my dwarven brethren, to whom i humbly offer a pint in apology), then don't pick a dwarf just because somebody told you they make the best rogues.<br><br>nimbledigits<br>leatherfoot raider of the 16th tier<br>mith marr<br><br>ps i'm not saying dwarves make poor rogues, just using them as an example.  pick a race you will want to play.     <br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
