<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99230667264889></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99230667264889><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=2&mid=99230667264889>RE: poison</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2&mid=99230667264889#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=64441><span id=Scholar>IvanTheTailBiter</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>60 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jun 11th 8:44 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Brewing has nothing to do with it.&nbsp;&nbsp;You get apply poison at 18 and it is of little use unless you buy poisons from a merchant or another player.  At 20 when you can make poison, you just need to train a point into it and it will start you around skill level 20 (same with apply poison if you train in it at level 20).<br><br>All you need to do is get some vials, suspension fluid and the proper reagents so you can make it in a morter and petistle (sp?).  If you are successful, then you get to apply it. If you successfully apply it, then you get to use it (assuming it does not get resisted).  Poison is a tough business to get going because you have to be successful making it, then applying it, and then using it.<br><br>good luck<br>&nbsp;<br>Be Safe in the Shadows:-)<br><br>~Ivan~<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
