	   <tr><td colspan=2>Rogue Ethics?!?&nbsp;&nbsp;What are you talking about?  The type of ethics you are refering to are the ethics of others, not rogues.  I mean come on.  How many thieves' have you heard of that lived very long by playing according to the rules of others.  Unless they are your friends (in which case I split the loot--like any rogue who wants to maintain friends would do) screw them.  You are a rogue, you kill for money, you steal from those who are less obsevervant than yourself, and you take advantage of the systems that have been put in place by others.  I say steal away.  You said that was Rathe Mountains where you are pping 15pp.  I will have to make my way over there soon, I could use the money.  Have fun and play your character--if it would bother him that others find his actions disgraceful than maybe he should change careers.  Again, just my two copper.<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
